    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a great start, really helps capture the sovereignty angle. to go a bit deeper for the students, could you expand on the economic side of it? specifically, how supporters would argue that strict enforcement actually protects domestic workers and prevents wage suppression in low-skilled sectors. i want them to be able to address the specific economic logic used by proponents.",
